Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: key-mon
Version: 0.16
Summary: A small utility to display your current keyboard and mouse status.  Useful for screencasts.
Home-page: http://code.google.com/p/key-mon
Author: Scott Kirkwood
Author-email: scott+keymon@forusers.com
License: LGPL
Download-URL: http://key-mon.googlecode.com/files/key-mons-0.16.zip
Description: Key-mon is useful for teaching since it shows the current status of your
        keyboard and mouse and you use them in another application.  No longer do you need to say
        'Now I'm pressing the Ctrl-D key', your students can just see the keystroke for themselves.
        
